s to heighten our understanding of great apes and the many ways they are like us. The reader will encounter apes living in human families, painting apes, apes who use American Sign Language, and chimpanzees who travelled in space.   A philosopher and historian specializing in primatology, Herzfeld offers thought-provoking insights about our perceptions of apes, as well as the boundary between "human" and "ape" and what it means to be either.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aApesxBehavior. 0aApesxPsychology. 0aHominidsxBehavior. 0aHominidsxPsychology. 0aHuman-animal relationships. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Zoology / Primatology.2bisacsh1 aFrey, Kevin1 aGoodall, Jane08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231656423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231656.jpg  a978-3-11-063898-1  YUP eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles